			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>Unifying and Generalizing Relations in Role-Based Data Modeling and Navigation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/DacoCHarkes.html">Daco C. Harkes</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_14">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_14</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagM">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> It proposes a language design for data modeling with first-class, n-ary, and bidirectional relations.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is presented as a domain-specific data modeling language with concise navigation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly bridges object-oriented navigation and relational querying by unifying their features.
</li></ul></li></ul>
